    "### Tutorial"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 1.1 Quickstart"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As a simple first example, we will use ELLIE to deliver a target pixel file (TPF) and light curve for a given TIC target."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import ellie"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First we load up the data for TIC 198591153, a relatively bright star (TESS mag = 9.0) observed in Sector 1. ELLIE is able to extract a light curve easily and automatically for such a bright, unblended object."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dp = ellie.data_products(tic=198591153)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now that we have a data product for our target, we simply call the individual_tpf() function, which will extract a target pixel file, perform aperture photometry with an automatically optimized aperture choice, and do some simple systematics corrections."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "postcard_1_3-3_0-4.fits\n",
      "*************\n",
      "You don't have the postcard your source is on. Here: we'll download it for you!\n",
      "*************\n",
      "*************\n",
      "We're doing our best to find the ideal aperture shape & size for your source.\n",
      "*************\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "WARNING: The \"exact\" method is not yet implemented for rectangular apertures -- using \"subpixel\" method with \"subpixels=32\" [photutils.aperture.core]\n",
      "  0%|          | 0/1 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "*************\n",
      "Please hold while we do some systematics corrections.\n",
      "*************\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  2.87it/s]\n",
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  4.90it/s]\n",
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  5.37it/s]\n",
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  4.62it/s]\n",
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  4.79it/s]\n",
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  4.68it/s]\n",
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  4.41it/s]\n",
      "100%|██████████| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  4.65it/s]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1296x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "tpf_fn = dp.individual_tpf()\n",
    "dp.plot()"
   ]
  },
